"For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Security<ept id=\"p1\">](../../../../docs/framework/wpf/security-wpf.md)</ept>.","pos":[10258,10343],"source":" For more information, see [Security](../../../../docs/framework/wpf/security-wpf.md)."},{"content":"When you use a <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser&gt;</ph> control in your application, WPF internally instantiates the native WebBrowser ActiveX control.","pos":[10350,10502],"source":"When you use a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser> control in your application, WPF internally instantiates the native WebBrowser ActiveX control."},{"content":"When your application is a partial-trust XBAP running in Internet Explorer, the ActiveX control runs in a dedicated thread of the Internet Explorer process.","pos":[10503,10659]},{"content":"Therefore, the following limitations apply:","pos":[10660,10703]},{"content":"The <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser&gt;</ph> control should provide behavior similar to the host browser, including security restrictions.","pos":[10713,10852],"source":"The <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser> control should provide behavior similar to the host browser, including security restrictions."},{"content":"Some of these security restrictions can be controlled through the Internet Explorer security settings.","pos":[10853,10955]},{"content":"For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Security<ept id=\"p1\">](../../../../docs/framework/wpf/security-wpf.md)</ept>.","pos":[10956,11041],"source":" For more information, see [Security](../../../../docs/framework/wpf/security-wpf.md)."},{"content":"An exception is thrown when an XBAP is loaded cross-domain in an HTML page.","pos":[11051,11126]},{"content":"Input is on a separate thread from the WPF <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser&gt;</ph>, so keyboard input cannot be intercepted and the IME state is not shared.","pos":[11136,11294],"source":"Input is on a separate thread from the WPF <xref:System.Windows.Controls.WebBrowser>, so keyboard input cannot be intercepted and the IME state is not shared."},{"content":"The timing or order of navigation may be different due to the ActiveX control running on another thread.","pos":[11304,11408]},{"content":"For example, navigating to a page is not always cancelled by starting another navigation request.","pos":[11409,11506]},{"content":"A custom ActiveX control may have trouble with communication since the WPF application is running in a separate thread.","pos":[11516,11635]},{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Interop.HwndHost.MessageHook&gt;</ph> does not get raised because <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Interop.HwndHost&gt;</ph> cannot subclass a window running in another thread or process.","pos":[11645,11825],"source":"<xref:System.Windows.Interop.HwndHost.MessageHook> does not get raised because <xref:System.Windows.Interop.HwndHost> cannot subclass a window running in another thread or process."},{"pos":[11835,11861],"content":"Creating a Full-Trust XBAP","linkify":"Creating a Full-Trust XBAP","nodes":[{"content":"Creating a Full-Trust XBAP","pos":[0,26]}]},{"content":"If your XBAP requires full trust, you can change your project to enable this permission.","pos":[11865,11953]},{"content":"The following steps describe how to enable full trust:","pos":[11954,12008]},{"content":"In Visual Studio, open the project properties.","pos":[12018,12064]},{"pos":[12074,12154],"content":"On the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Security<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> tab, select the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>This is a full trust application<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> option.","source":"On the **Security** tab, select the **This is a full trust application** option."},{"content":"This setting makes the following changes:","pos":[12161,12202]},{"pos":[12212,12289],"content":"In the project file, the <ph id=\"ph1\">`&lt;TargetZone&gt;`</ph> element value is changed to <ph id=\"ph2\">`Custom`</ph>.","source":"In the project file, the `<TargetZone>` element value is changed to `Custom`."},{"pos":[12299,12418],"content":"In the application manifest (app.manifest), an <ph id=\"ph1\">`Unrestricted=\"true\"`</ph> attribute is added to the <ph id=\"ph2\">`PermissionSet`</ph> element.","source":"In the application manifest (app.manifest), an `Unrestricted=\"true\"` attribute is added to the `PermissionSet` element."},{"pos":[12624,12651],"content":"Deploying a Full-Trust XBAP","linkify":"Deploying a Full-Trust XBAP","nodes":[{"content":"Deploying a Full-Trust XBAP","pos":[0,27]}]},{"content":"When you deploy a full-trust XBAP that does not follow the ClickOnce Trusted Deployment model, the behavior when the user runs the application will depend on the security zone.","pos":[12655,12831]},{"content":"In some cases, the user will receive a warning when they attempt to install it.","pos":[12832,12911]},{"content":"The user can choose to continue or cancel the installation.","pos":[12912,12971]},{"content":"The following table describes the behavior of the application for each security zone and what you have to do for the application to receive full trust.","pos":[12972,13123]},{"content":"Security Zone","pos":[13130,13143]},{"content":"Behavior","pos":[13144,13152]},{"content":"Getting Full Trust","pos":[13153,13171]},{"content":"Local computer","pos":[13240,13254]},{"content":"Automatic full trust","pos":[13255,13275]},{"content":"No action is needed.","pos":[13276,13296]},{"content":"Intranet and trusted sites","pos":[13301,13327]},{"content":"Prompt for full trust","pos":[13328,13349]},{"content":"Sign the XBAP with a certificate so that the user sees the source in the prompt.","pos":[13350,13430]},{"content":"Internet","pos":[13435,13443]},{"content":"Fails with \"Trust Not Granted\"","pos":[13444,13474]},{"content":"Sign the XBAP with a certificate.","pos":[13475,13508]},{"pos":[13517,13655],"content":"[!NOTE]\n The behavior described in the previous table is for full-trust XBAPs that do not follow the ClickOnce Trusted Deployment model.","leadings":["","> "],"nodes":[{"content":"The behavior described in the previous table is for full-trust XBAPs that do not follow the ClickOnce Trusted Deployment model.","pos":[9,136]}]},{"content":"It is recommended that you use the ClickOnce Trusted Deployment model for deploying a full-trust XBAP.","pos":[13662,13764]},{"content":"This model allows your XBAP to be granted full trust automatically, regardless of the security zone, so that the user is not prompted.","pos":[13765,13899]},{"content":"As part of this model, you must sign your application with a certificate from a trusted publisher.","pos":[13900,13998]},{"content":"For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Trusted Application Deployment Overview<ept id=\"p1\">](/visualstudio/deployment/trusted-application-deployment-overview)</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Introduction to Code Signing<ept id=\"p2\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=166327)</ept>.","pos":[13999,14215],"source":" For more information, see [Trusted Application Deployment Overview](/visualstudio/deployment/trusted-application-deployment-overview) and [Introduction to Code Signing](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=166327)."},{"pos":[14285,14327],"content":"XBAP Start Time Performance Considerations","linkify":"XBAP Start Time Performance Considerations","nodes":[{"content":"XBAP Start Time Performance Considerations","pos":[0,42]}]},{"content":"An important aspect of XBAP performance is its start time.","pos":[14331,14389]},{"content":"If an XBAP is the first WPF application to load, the <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>cold start<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> time can be ten seconds or more.","pos":[14390,14488],"source":" If an XBAP is the first WPF application to load, the *cold start* time can be ten seconds or more."},{"content":"This is because the progress page is rendered by WPF, and both the CLR and WPF must be cold-started to display the application.","pos":[14489,14616]},{"content":"Starting in <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v35SP1_short](../../../../includes/net-v35sp1-short-md.md)]</ph>, XBAP cold-start time is mitigated by displaying an unmanaged progress page early in the deployment cycle.","pos":[14623,14815],"source":"Starting in [!INCLUDE[net_v35SP1_short](../../../../includes/net-v35sp1-short-md.md)], XBAP cold-start time is mitigated by displaying an unmanaged progress page early in the deployment cycle."},{"content":"The progress page appears almost immediately after the application is started, because it is displayed by native hosting code and rendered in HTML.","pos":[14816,14963]},{"content":"In addition, improved concurrency of the <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[ndptecclick](../../../../includes/ndptecclick-md.md)]</ph> download sequence improves the start time by up to ten percent.","pos":[14970,15138],"source":"In addition, improved concurrency of the [!INCLUDE[ndptecclick](../../../../includes/ndptecclick-md.md)] download sequence improves the start time by up to ten percent."},{"content":"After <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[ndptecclick](../../../../includes/ndptecclick-md.md)]</ph> downloads and validates manifests, the application download starts, and the progress bar starts to update.","pos":[15139,15315],"source":" After [!INCLUDE[ndptecclick](../../../../includes/ndptecclick-md.md)] downloads and validates manifests, the application download starts, and the progress bar starts to update."},{"pos":[15324,15332],"content":"See Also","linkify":"See Also","nodes":[{"content":"See Also","pos":[0,8]}]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Configure Visual Studio to Debug a XAML Browser Application to Call a Web Service<ept id=\"p1\">](../../../../docs/framework/wpf/app-development/configure-vs-to-debug-a-xaml-browser-to-call-a-web-service.md)</ept><ph id=\"ph1\"> </ph>","pos":[15336,15530],"source":"[Configure Visual Studio to Debug a XAML Browser Application to Call a Web Service](../../../../docs/framework/wpf/app-development/configure-vs-to-debug-a-xaml-browser-to-call-a-web-service.md) "},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Deploying a WPF Application<ept id=\"p1\">](../../../../docs/framework/wpf/app-development/deploying-a-wpf-application-wpf.md)</ept>","pos":[15534,15646],"source":"[Deploying a WPF Application](../../../../docs/framework/wpf/app-development/deploying-a-wpf-application-wpf.md)"}]}